# ProjectGarage - Project Context

You are working on ProjectGarage, a Next.js 15 car buying assistant app.

## Tech Stack
- Next.js 15 (App Router only, no Pages Router)
- React 19
- TypeScript (strict mode)
- Tailwind CSS v4
- shadcn/ui components
- Lucide-React icons
- Vercel hosting (free tier)

## Data Strategy: 3-Tier Hybrid API

```
1. NHTSA vPIC API (free) → Make/model validation, always current
2. CarQuery API (free)   → Detailed specs, best for 1995-2022
3. Claude AI fallback    → New cars 2023+, label as "AI-Generated"
```

## Architecture: Hybrid (Atomic UI + Feature-based Business Logic)

```
src/
├── app/                    # Routes only, minimal logic
├── features/               # Business logic modules
│   └── [feature]/
│       ├── components/     # Feature-specific UI
│       ├── hooks/
│       ├── services/       # API calls
│       ├── actions/        # Server Actions
│       └── types.ts
├── shared/
│   └── ui/                 # Atomic Design
│       ├── atoms/          # Button, Input, Badge
│       ├── molecules/      # SearchInput, StatDisplay
│       └── organisms/      # Header, Footer
├── lib/                    # Utilities (utils.ts, storage.ts)
└── types/                  # Shared types
```

## Naming Conventions
- Directories: `kebab-case`
- Components: `PascalCase.tsx`
- Hooks: `use-camel-case.ts`
- Types: `PascalCaseSuffix` (ButtonProps, CarResponse, CreateCarInput)

## Current Version: V1
Focus: Single car lookup, basic/advanced specs, localStorage history, Vercel deployment.
See `ROADMAP.md` for full version plan and API documentation.
